<title>
APP Sensor On-Vehicle Inspection
</title>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not drop or otherwise expose accelerator pedal assembly (incorporating APP sensor) to large shock. Any accelerator pedal assembly that has received large shock must be replaced.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Keep APP sensor section of accelerator pedal assembly free from water and oil.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not disassemble accelerator pedal assembly (incorporating APP sensor).
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
After replacing accelerator pedal assembly (incorporating APP sensor), calibrate throttle valve position. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1306004"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that accelerator pedal assembly (incorporating APP sensor) has been mounted to vehicle body properly (no pinched floor carpet, etc.).
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If mounting is improper, reinstall accelerator pedal assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1306006"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Connect scan tool to DLC with ignition “OFF”.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
 Set ignition “ON” and select “Data List” mode.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Check that voltage varies depending on accelerator pedal position as shown in the following graph.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, check the following points.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Wire harness and connections
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
APP sensor 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENCP70A1306007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
